data_cleaning_customer_personality_analysis.ipynb
üéØ Objective
To clean and prepare a raw dataset by handling missing values, duplicates, inconsistent formatting, and data type issues to ensure it is ready for analysis.

üõ†Ô∏è Tools Used
Python (Pandas) for data manipulation

Jupyter Notebook / Google Colab

(Optional: Excel for manual inspection or small datasets)

üìÅ Dataset Used
Customer Personality Analysis (from Kaggle)

üîß Steps Performed
Handling Missing Values

Used .isnull().sum() to identify missing data.

Removed or imputed null values using:

df.dropna() for rows with too many missing fields.

df.fillna() for columns where imputation made sense (e.g., using mean, median, or mode).

Removing Duplicates

Identified duplicates using df.duplicated().

Removed them using df.drop_duplicates().

Standardizing Text Values

Converted text columns (like Gender, Country) to consistent formats:

Used .str.lower().str.strip() to remove extra spaces and unify casing.

Replaced inconsistent labels using .replace() (e.g., "M" and "Male" standardized to "male").

Date Format Consistency

Converted date columns (like Dt_Customer) to datetime using pd.to_datetime().

Standardized format to dd-mm-yyyy.

Renaming Columns

Renamed columns to be lowercase, snake_case, and removed spaces:

Example: "Income" ‚Üí "income", "Education Level" ‚Üí "education_level"

Done using df.columns = df.columns.str.lower().str.replace(' ', '_')

Fixing Data Types

Ensured columns had the correct data types:

Age as int

Income as float

Date fields as datetime

‚úÖ Deliverables
Cleaned Dataset: cleaned_customer_personality.csv

Notebook: data_cleaning_customer_personality.ipynb

Summary of Changes:

Dropped 152 null values in Income

Standardized 3 gender categories into 2

Removed 4 duplicate rows

Converted Dt_Customer to datetime format

Renamed all column headers for consistency

Ensured correct data types for analysis

üìå Notes
